Display some content.

Source: R/pioDisp.R
pioDisp.Rd

This function tries to convert almost everything to `tibble` data structure, so that we can exploit their nice layout functions.

pioDisp(x)

Arguments

x

Content to display

Value

Nothing.

Examples

M = matrix(1:100, ncol = 10)
M[1,4] = NA
pioDisp(M)
#> # A tibble: 10 x 10
#>       V1    V2    V3    V4    V5    V6    V7    V8    V9   V10
